[[File:Bas Eenhoorn (Nationaal Commissaris Digitale Overheid) bij het Symposium Actieve Openbaarheid 03 (cropped).jpg|thumb|200px|right|Bas Eenhoorn]]
'''Herman Bastiaan (Bas) Eenhoorn''' (born September 14, 1946 in [[Groningen (city)|Groningen]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] politician and former [[civil servant]]. He is a member of the [[People's Party for Freedom and Democracy]] (Volkspartij voor Vrijheid en Democratie). He currently serves as [[waarnemend burgemeester|interim mayor]] of [[Vlaardingen]]. Previously he was mayor of [[Alphen Aan Den Rijn]], [[Schiermonnikoog (island and municipality)|Schiermonnikoog]] (1976–1983) and [[Voorburg]] (1983–1996) as well as acting mayor of [[Lansingerland]] (2007) and [[Kaag en Braassem]] (2009–2010).<ref>{{nl}} [http://www.alphenaandenrijn.nl/smartsite.shtml?ch=INT&id=76269 Waarnemend burgemeester] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719062259/http://www.alphenaandenrijn.nl/smartsite.shtml?ch=INT&id=76269 |date=July 19, 2011 }} Announcement on the official site of Alphen aan den Rijn. (Retrieved April 2011)</ref>
Eenhoorn became well-known after giving press conferences in his function as acting mayor after the [[Alphen aan den Rijn shopping mall shooting]] on April 9, 2011.<ref>[http://hosted2.ap.org/APDEFAULT/contact/Article_2011-04-09-EU-Netherlands-Mall-Shooting/id-ec81b87b589048f4a76878a218f914e1 News Report] from the Associated Press</ref>
Eenhoorn studied [[social geography|social]] and [[economic geography]] with a specialization in [[public administration]] at the [[University of Groningen]].
