{{main|Pula Film Festival}}

The '''Golden Arena for Best Director''' ''([[Croatian language|Croatian]]: Zlatna arena za režiju'') is an award given for best director at the [[Pula Film Festival]], which was until 1992 the [[SFR Yugoslavia|Yugoslav]] equivalent of the [[Academy Awards]]. Since 1992 and the [[breakup of Yugoslavia]] the competition narrowed to [[Croatia]]n films only. The first festival was held in 1954, but the award was introduced in 1955.

